  • Constructor Details

    • SurfaceCollection

      public SurfaceCollection​(double[][] bottomPolygon, double[][] topPolygon)
      Create multiple surfaces from a prism. Bottom and top polygons are given. The surface collection contains top, bottom and all side rectangles.
      Parameters:
      bottomPolygon - bottom polygon, counter-clockwise form top view
      topPolygon - top polygon, counter-clockwise form top view

    • SurfaceCollection

      public SurfaceCollection​(double[][][] surfaces, double[][] vertexes)
      Create a surface collection. Surface planes are computed on creation. If a surface separates free from 'inner mass' of an object, the points must go counter clockwise viewed from free space.
      Parameters:
      surfaces - array of surfaces, each a polyon
      vertexes - array of vertexes, each vertex only once

    • SurfaceCollection

      public SurfaceCollection​(double[][][] surfaces, double[][][] surfacePlanes)
      Create a surface collection. Surface planes are passed.
      Parameters:
      surfaces - array of surfaces, each a polyon
      surfacePlanes - plane for each surface as computed by Geom.getPlane(double[][])
